data.using-a-different-cookie#Using a Differe:
bard-ai v2 comes with the ability to use cookies from different Google users. These will take the form of a __Secure-#PSID with a non-one number. If you wish to use such a cookie, simply prefix your COOKIE with __Secure-#PSID= (with your number), like this.
import Bard from "bard-ai";

let myBard = new Bard("__Secure-3PSID=MY_COOKIE");

data.config#Config:
Pass in a configuration JSON, like this:
let myBard = new Bard(COOKIE, {
verbose: true,
fetch: fetch,
context: "Answer this like a pirate: "
});

Config Option	Type	Description	verbose	boolean	Log information about what is happening	fetch	function	Any fetch polyfill. Ensure it has the same interface as browser fetch.	context	string	Instructions prefixed before every request.

data.return-structure#Return Structure:
{
"content": string,
"images": [
{
tag: string,
url: string,
info: {
raw: string,
source: string,
website: string,
favicon: string
}
},
...
],
"ids": object
}
Let's walk through what each one of these properties is.
Property Name	Type	Description	content	string	The Markdown return value of Bard	images	array	Array of objects, representing the image. See Image JSON below	ids	object	An object that is used to import/export conversations.

